                    	<note xml:id="n_transcrSource" type="transcrSource">
                    	    
<p xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">Original manuscript</p>
                    	</note>
                    
                    
                    	<note xml:id="n_dating" type="dating">
                    	    
    <p xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">Considering that Van Gogh copied on these loose sheets both hymn 180:5 and Ten Kate’s ‘Zucht naar heiliging’ (A longing for sanctification) – both of which occur in <ref target="let090.xml">letter 90</ref>, which dates from the beginning of September 1876 – we assume that the sheet originated in approximately that month. In <hi rend="italics">De brieven</hi> 1990 these sheets were appended to <ref target="let104.xml">letter 104</ref>, but we see no reason to connect them with that letter. </p>
                    	</note>
                    
                    
                    
